I"(<p>Types of information that may be transmitted via wireless networks and devices with or without encryption including mission critical information or sensitive personal information.</p>

<p>State organizations shall not transmit confidential information via a wireless connection to, or from a portable computing device unless encryption methods, such as a Virtual Private Network (VPN), Wi-Fi Protected Access, or other secure encryption protocols that meet appropriate protection or certification standards, are used to protect the information.</p>
